<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 03 at 4:14PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Pittsylvania County and the City of Danville through 445 PM EDT...
At 413 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Westover Hills, or over Danville, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Danville...
Blairs...
Ringgold...
Westover Hills...
and Keeling.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
